# Data Ingestion Conventions

## Tier overview
| Tier | Type              | Schedule | Sources                                                      |
|------|-------------------|----------|--------------------------------------------------------------|
| 1    | Manual seed       | Once     | `data/seed/internships_seed.json` → Supabase                 |
| 2    | Structured feeds  | Daily    | Devpost RSS, DoraHacks API, MLH iCal                         |
| 3    | Playwright scrape | Weekly   | LFX Mentorship, GSoC, Outreachy, Hyperledger, LFN, Open Mainframe |
| 4    | Discovery         | Daily    | Google Custom Search API (10–15 queries/day, free tier)      |

## Mandatory fields on every upserted row
```json
{ "name": "...", "url": "...", "type": "...", "source": "...", "reviewed": false }
```
`reviewed` MUST be `false` from scripts. Admin approves in-app. Never set `true` programmatically.

## Upsert key
Upsert on `url` (unique constraint). On conflict, update `updated_at` and any changed fields.
Never insert a duplicate URL.

## Source field values — use exactly
| Script / feed           | `source` value          |
|-------------------------|-------------------------|
| Seed script             | `manual`                |
| Devpost RSS             | `devpost_rss`           |
| DoraHacks JSON API      | `dorahacks_api`         |
| MLH iCal                | `mlh_ical`              |
| LFX Playwright          | `playwright_lfx`        |
| GSoC Playwright         | `playwright_gsoc`       |
| Outreachy Playwright    | `playwright_outreachy`  |
| Hyperledger Playwright  | `playwright_hyperledger`|
| LFN Playwright          | `playwright_lfn`        |
| Custom Search discovery | `custom_search`         |

## nigeria_eligible heuristic
Set `nigeria_eligible = true` if description/eligibility text includes any of:
`worldwide`, `global`, `open to all`, `international`, `Africa`, `Nigeria`, `sub-saharan`
Set `nigeria_eligible = null` (unknown) if eligibility text is absent or ambiguous.
Admin resolves during review queue. Never assume false.

## Security
```bash
# All scripts read from environment — never hardcode
SUPABASE_URL=...              # from GitHub Actions secrets
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=... # from GitHub Actions secrets
GOOGLE_CSE_API_KEY=...        # Custom Search API key
GOOGLE_CSE_CX=...             # Programmable Search Engine ID
```
Scripts must `process.exit(1)` (Node) or `sys.exit(1)` (Python) on any Supabase write failure
so the GitHub Actions run is marked failed and visible in the dashboard.

## DoraHacks API
Endpoint: `GET https://dorahacks.io/api/hackathon/list/`
Returns structured JSON with `title`, `start_time`, `end_time`, `prize_pool`, `is_online`.
Map `is_online: true` → `remote: true`. `prize_pool > 0` → `stipend_usd: prize_pool` (approximate).

## Discovery layer (Tier 4)
- Google Custom Search JSON API with a Programmable Search Engine configured across programme/fellowship domains
- Daily budget: 10–15 queries (free tier cap: 100/day)
- Sample queries:
  - `"open source fellowship 2026 stipend"`
  - `"hackathon 2026 Nigeria remote"`
  - `"developer programme 2026 application open"`
- Pipeline: search → deduplicate against existing `url` values → fetch + parse each new page → upsert with `source: 'custom_search'`, `reviewed: false`
- For complex page parsing, an optional Claude API call extracts structured fields

## scripts/ folder structure
```
scripts/
  seed/
    parse_internships.py       # Tier 1: parse internships.txt → JSON → Supabase
    internships_seed.json      # generated intermediate (not committed if large)
  ingest/
    devpost_rss.mjs            # Tier 2
    dorahacks_api.mjs          # Tier 2
    mlh_ical.mjs               # Tier 2
    lfx_scrape.mjs             # Tier 3 (Playwright)
    gsoc_scrape.mjs            # Tier 3
    outreachy_scrape.mjs       # Tier 3
    hyperledger_scrape.mjs     # Tier 3
  discovery/
    custom_search.mjs          # Tier 4
  lib/
    supabase_client.mjs        # shared: createClient(url, serviceRoleKey)
    nigeria_heuristic.mjs      # shared: classifyNigeriaEligibility(text)
    upsert.mjs                 # shared: upsertProgramme(client, data)
```
